===Nagasaki mission crew=== [[File:Bocks-Car-enlisted-flight-crew.png|right|thumb|Crew C-15. front row: Dehart, Kuharek, Buckley, Gallagher, Spitzer; back row: Olivi, Beahan, Sweeney, Van Pelt, Albury]] Crew C-15 (normally assigned to ''[[The Great Artiste]]''):<ref name="Eyewitness"/>{{sfn|Campbell|2005|pp=141–142}} *Major [[Charles W. Sweeney]], Aircraft Commander, North Quincy, MA *Captain [[Charles Donald Albury|Charles Donald "Don" Albury]], Co-pilot (pilot of Crew C-15), Miami, FL *Second Lieutenant Frederick "Fred" J. Olivi, Regular Co-pilot *Captain James F. Van Pelt, Jr., Navigator, Oak Hill, WV *Captain [[Kermit Beahan|Kermit K. Beahan]], Bombardier, Houston, TX *Master Sergeant John D. Kuharek, Flight Engineer, Sharpsburg, PA *Staff Sergeant Raymond C. Gallagher, Gunner, assistant flight engineer, Chicago, IL *Staff Sergeant Edward K. Buckley, Radar Operator, Lisbon, OH *Sergeant Abe M. Spitzer, Radio Operator, Bronx, NY *Sergeant Albert T. "Pappy" DeHart, Tail Gunner, Plainview, TX
Also on board were the following additional mission personnel:<ref name="Eyewitness"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hiroshima-remembered.com/history/nagasaki/page3.html |title=The Story of Nagasaki |publisher=National Science Digital Library |accessdate=28 March 2013}}</ref> *[[Commander (United States)|Commander]] [[Frederick Ashworth]], [[United States Navy|USN]], Weaponeer *[[Lieutenant (navy)|Lieutenant]] Philip M. Barnes, USN, Assistant Weaponeer *Second Lieutenant [[Jacob Beser]], Radar Countermeasures, Baltimore, MD (Lt. Beser flew on ''both'' atomic missions, serving as the radar countermeasures crewman on the ''[[Enola Gay]]'', August 6, 1945, and ''Bockscar'', August 9, 1945).
